OPEN SYSTEM THEORY APPROACH TO LIBRARY EFFECTIVENESS.BRIEFLY DISCUSSES THE MEASUREMENT OF LIBRARY EFFECTIVENESS USING THE OPENSYSTEM THEORY OF ORGANISATIONS AND A MODEL FOR EVALUATION OF ACADEMICLIBRARIES APPROPRIATE TO THE OPEN SYSTEM. DISCUSSES THE RESULTS OF A 1955RESEARCH PROJECT IN WHICH THEY WERE USED (EVALUATION OF COLLEGE LIBRARIES FORACCREDITATION PURPOSES, BY ALAN DALE COVEY, STANFORD UNIVERSITY EDDDISSERTATION) AND MAKES SUGGESTIONS FOR FUTURE RESEARCH IN THIS AREA